d cooler fermentation). Czech lagers are traditionally made with  decoction mashes (often double decoction), even with modern malts, while most modern German lagers are made with infusion or  step infusion mashes. These differences characterize the richness, mouthfeel, and flavor profile that distinguishes Czech lagers. ",
